Subject: [PATCH] v8: guard unused is_code label in jitless arm64 builtins

With v8_enable_lite_mode (V8_JITLESS), the CODE_TYPE dispatch entry and
the is_code bind in GetSharedFunctionInfoBytecodeOrBaseline are compiled
out behind !V8_JITLESS_BOOL, but the Label itself was declared
unconditionally. Chromium builds with -Werror, so -Wunused-variable
breaks the jitless build. Guard the declaration the same way as its uses.
---
--- a/v8/src/builtins/arm64/builtins-arm64.cc
+++ b/v8/src/builtins/arm64/builtins-arm64.cc
@@ -402,7 +402,10 @@ static void GetSharedFunctionInfoBytecodeOrBaseline(
     Label* is_baseline, Label* is_unavailable) {
   ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
   DCHECK(!AreAliased(bytecode, scratch1));
-  Label is_interpreter_data, is_bytecode_array, is_code;
+  Label is_interpreter_data, is_bytecode_array;
+#if !V8_JITLESS_BOOL
+  Label is_code;
+#endif

   Register data = bytecode;
   __ LoadTrustedUnknownPointerField(
